HEADWORD: Tongue-shaped
<hw>Tongue"-shaped`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Shaped like a
tongue; specifically <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, linear or oblong, and fleshy,
blunt at the end, and convex beneath; <as>as, a <ex>tongue-shaped</ex>
leaf</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tongue-shell</ent>⟦br⟧
